Miners throughout the world have used strikes not only to achieve economic gains, but 
also to gain greater control over their industries and to achieve political ends.  In addition 
to higher wages, miners in the Soviet Union struck for more local control of their industry 
and in Poland miners struck for the legalization of Solidarity.</SUM>
